the 26,000 year cycle

00:07:18.640 --> 00:07:25.030 align:middle line:10%
approximately into five
5,125 year long cycles.

00:07:25.030 --> 00:07:29.410 align:middle line:10%
Each of those cycles
when they begin something

00:07:29.410 --> 00:07:32.090 align:middle line:10%
happens to the civilization
during that time.

00:07:32.090 --> 00:07:34.900 align:middle line:84%
And one of the questions
that historians have asked

00:07:34.900 --> 00:07:38.620 align:middle line:84%
is, could there be something
that drives these cycles?

00:07:38.620 --> 00:07:40.420 align:middle line:84%
Is there a cosmological
phenomenon?

00:07:40.420 --> 00:07:42.010 align:middle line:90%
Is there a climactic phenomenon?

00:07:42.010 --> 00:07:44.200 align:middle line:90%
Is there a geologic phenomenon?

00:07:44.200 --> 00:07:47.150 align:middle line:84%
Maybe it's a convergence
of all of these phenomenon,

00:07:47.150 --> 00:07:51.520 align:middle line:84%
something happens
every 5,125 years.

00:07:51.520 --> 00:07:54.610 align:middle line:84%
Well, if we take
the year 2012 is

00:07:54.610 --> 00:08:01.990 align:middle line:84%
the end of one 5,125 year long
cycle and we go back in time

00:08:01.990 --> 00:08:05.320 align:middle line:84%
to the 5,000 years
previously, this

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:08.260 align:middle line:84%
would be the time
